-- #194 fallback regression: an UNSIGNATURED constrained free function DEFINED here
-- and CALLED from another module.  Its body dispatches `+` (Num) at its quantified
-- parameter, so it infers `Num a => a -> a` with NO signature — the promotion shape.
-- discoverPromotedModules must promote `dbl`/`quad` and seed their cross-module
-- inferred arities (crossModuleFunConstraintsRef) so the CALLER module's call sites
-- get the leading dict argument.  This is the multi-module analogue of
-- prelude_shadow_constrained, exercising the elaborateModules NON-EMPTY-harvest
-- fallback path (a directly-promoted fn ⇒ discard the bare sweep, run 2-pass).
export dbl x = x + x

-- a second promoted fn that CALLS the first (transitive promotion within the module):
-- `quad` inherits `Num a =>` from `dbl`.
export quad x = dbl (dbl x)
